Feature/style conventions

pull_request.title: Feature/style conventions
pull_request.body:
Changes made:

- Public members should use PascalCasing
- All methods should use PascalCasing
- // Comments should start with a space and a capital letter
- ID when camelCased or PascalCased is Id
- Added spacing for readability in certain methods
- Curly braces should be on new lines generally
- When it is obvious what a type is var should be used
